<br>
I am interested in joining the ranks of AD and was told to post on the recruitment thread, so here I am. First of all, I am a multiboxer, I have 4 cpu's at home with 4 accounts. Currently I play the following...<br>
<br>
Krossover 60 Ogre Warrior<br>
Kahleen 60 High Elf Cleric<br>
Wuulfram 57 Wood Elf Druid<br>
<br>
However, I am working on an enchanter to replace the druid as my third. Cascia keeps calling me Warhoundt 2 for some reason....<br>
<br>
I am currently the GM of a guild named Descendants of Prime. DoP is a guild composed of RL friends from the Southwest area of Missouri. We have a membership of 19, average level of 41. Ultimately it is a small guild, we created it to have fun and adventure together. Therein lies the problem....<br>
<br>
I have more free time than my guildmates and greater resources as well. I have outleveled my friends and have been stuck doing the same things over and over. Cascia and I became friends about 6 months ago and because of Cascia I have been able to experience new and exciting things that I would not have been able to otherwise. After discussing with my friends in person, they support my decision to pursue a spot in Ascending Dawn. They truely are my friends and realize that this would allow me to meet new people and see new things. I have attended a few AD events, 3 killings of Dain, 1 Tunare (thanks for the whip), and a few ventures into SSRA with members of AD. After these experiences with good people that really know what they were doing, I think that AD is the organization that I would really like to become a part of.  <br>
<br>
I will be spending as much time as I can in SSRA to get to know as many AD people as I can... along with that, if there are any of you that need a cleric/druid/warrior at anytime, please feel free to ask. I am usually just avoiding Cascia..... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As a tribute to my friends and the organization that I was once a part of, I would like to keep my DoP tag throughout any recruitment process that I may endure. If this is any problem at all, this can be changed. It is kind of a last hurrah for the times we have spent together. <br>
<br>
If you have any questions, please contact me in game on Krossover's screen, it is the one I am usually looking at. Also, you can email me at rog_irie@hotmail.com.<br>
<br>
Thank you very much for your time,<br>
<br>
